==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Chare
<hw>Chare</hw>, }</mhw> <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[See
3d <er>Char</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To perform; to do; to
finish.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Nores.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thet char is <qex>chared</qex>, as the good wife said when she had
hanged her husband.</q> <rj><qau>Old Proverb.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To work or hew, as stone.</def> <rj><au>Oxf.
Gloss.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chare</ent>⟦br⟧
